WEBVTT

00:01.983 --> 00:05.085
<i>[rock music]</i>

00:05.087 --> 00:09.356
<i>♪</i>

00:09.358 --> 00:12.059
<i>- And finally,</i>
<i>the motion to ration shampoo</i>

00:12.061 --> 00:15.029
due to chronic shortages
passed...

00:15.031 --> 00:16.463
by a hair!

00:16.465 --> 00:17.665
[laughs]
[all groan]

00:17.667 --> 00:21.802
- So the minutes from our last
meeting are approved.

00:21.804 --> 00:23.771
Any new business?

00:23.773 --> 00:26.974
Anyone?
Anyone?

00:26.976 --> 00:28.042
No one?
- Lori!

00:28.044 --> 00:29.777
- I'm just messing with you.

00:29.779 --> 00:31.478
Lincoln has the floor.

00:31.480 --> 00:32.713
- As you all know,
our annual trip

00:32.715 --> 00:36.116
to Scratchy Bottom Campgrounds
is quickly approaching.

00:36.118 --> 00:37.051
[all groan]

00:37.053 --> 00:38.886
- That place is the worst.

00:38.888 --> 00:41.021
Bears always steal our food.

00:41.023 --> 00:41.722
- [roars]

00:41.724 --> 00:44.592
- And we have to sleep
on the hard ground.

00:44.594 --> 00:46.060
- And poop in the woods.

00:46.062 --> 00:46.961
- I like pooping in the woods.

00:46.963 --> 00:51.599
- And the Dipterum Culicidae are
the size of Mustelas Nivalis.

00:51.601 --> 00:52.900
[crickets chirping]

00:52.902 --> 00:55.469
The mosquitoes are the size
of weasels.

00:55.471 --> 00:58.772
- And don't forget the scary
hill people hiding in the trees.

00:58.774 --> 01:01.976
- There's no such thing
as hill people, Lincoln.

01:01.978 --> 01:02.743
- My point is,

01:02.745 --> 01:06.680
why can't we go someplace
different like Aloha Beach

01:06.682 --> 01:08.449
or Dairyland Amusement Park?

01:08.451 --> 01:11.018
- Because Mom and Dad
will never go for it.

01:11.020 --> 01:13.787
- How do we know?
We've never asked.

01:13.789 --> 01:16.690
[overlapping chatter]

01:16.692 --> 01:17.224
- Fine.

01:17.226 --> 01:21.729
All in favor of Lincoln wasting
his time and asking Mom and Dad?

01:21.731 --> 01:23.764
[sighs]
Motion passes.

01:23.766 --> 01:26.133
- Fine with us, sweetie.
- Sure, son.

01:26.135 --> 01:27.701
I don't see why not.

01:27.703 --> 01:29.870
[all cheering]

01:29.872 --> 01:31.071
- So which is it?

01:31.073 --> 01:32.706
Aloha Beach or Dairyland?

01:32.708 --> 01:34.108
- Oh, they didn't say.

01:34.110 --> 01:36.543
I guess it's up to us
to decide.

01:36.545 --> 01:38.812
All in favor of Aloha Beach?

01:38.814 --> 01:39.880
One, two, three, four, five.

01:39.882 --> 01:42.650
- You want to go to the beach,
Lucy?

01:42.652 --> 01:43.684
- Two words.

01:43.686 --> 01:44.918
Shark attacks.

01:44.920 --> 01:46.687
- All in favor of Dairyland?

01:46.689 --> 01:47.755
One, two, three, four, five.

01:47.757 --> 01:50.924
- It's five against five.
We win!

01:50.926 --> 01:52.626
- It's a tie, Leni.

01:52.628 --> 01:53.727
- Wait a minute.

01:53.729 --> 01:54.895
Lincoln didn't vote.

01:54.897 --> 01:57.064
- Well, Lincoln,
what's it gonna be?

01:57.066 --> 01:58.899
- It's so hard to choose.

01:58.901 --> 02:00.834
I really like the beach...

02:00.836 --> 02:03.103
[overlapping chatter]

02:03.105 --> 02:05.139
But I love Dairyland.

02:05.141 --> 02:08.008
[overlapping chatter]

02:08.009 --> 02:10.176
I don't know.
I can't decide.

02:10.179 --> 02:11.078
I need more time.

02:11.080 --> 02:12.780
Can I have till the end
of the day?

02:12.782 --> 02:14.214
- Really?
- Fine.

02:14.216 --> 02:17.685
You have until the end
of the day to decide.

02:17.687 --> 02:18.719
[bangs table]

02:18.721 --> 02:20.020
- [sighs]

02:20.022 --> 02:20.921
Now I've done it.

02:20.923 --> 02:23.691
If I choose Aloha Beach,
five of my sisters

02:23.693 --> 02:24.625
are gonna be mad at me,

02:24.627 --> 02:27.494
and if I choose Dairyland,
the other five will be mad.

02:27.496 --> 02:29.863
Making a decision
is gonna be rough.

02:29.865 --> 02:31.732
- Hey, Linky.

02:31.734 --> 02:33.500
I brought you something.

02:33.502 --> 02:36.170
A short stack
from your favorite short stack.

02:36.172 --> 02:40.240
You should never make a big
decision on an empty stomach.

02:40.242 --> 02:43.110
- Wow.
Thanks, Lola.

02:43.112 --> 02:44.144
- Hey, little bro.

02:44.146 --> 02:46.814
I was just thinking,
with all the pressure

02:46.816 --> 02:48.615
you're under to decide,

02:48.617 --> 02:52.052
maybe a massage
would help you relax.

02:52.054 --> 02:53.921
Hiya!

02:53.923 --> 02:58.625
- [voice shaking]
Uh, this is awkward.

02:58.627 --> 02:59.326
Down a little.

02:59.328 --> 03:04.565
I carry most of my stress
in my lower back.

03:04.567 --> 03:06.233
Ahh.

03:07.168 --> 03:08.902
- Shower time.
- Huh?

03:08.904 --> 03:10.871
- Take a nice long one.

03:10.873 --> 03:13.173
I cleared the bathroom schedule.
- Wait.

03:13.175 --> 03:15.042
You guys aren't trying
to get my vote

03:15.044 --> 03:17.211
for Aloha Beach,
are you?

03:17.213 --> 03:18.545
both: No.
- No, no, no.

03:18.547 --> 03:20.013
- Wait, I thought we were.

03:20.015 --> 03:21.715
[sighing together]

03:21.717 --> 03:24.318
<i>[mechanical whirring]</i>

03:24.886 --> 03:25.753
- Cleaning my room?

03:25.755 --> 03:27.788
You guys aren't trying
to get my vote

03:27.790 --> 03:29.590
for Dairyland, are you?

03:29.592 --> 03:30.691
- What? No.
- No, no.

03:30.693 --> 03:34.695
- Now that's funny.
- Of course we are.

03:34.697 --> 03:36.296
- I amend my earlier statement.

03:36.298 --> 03:38.699
Deciding on where to go
for our vacation

03:38.701 --> 03:42.302
might not be so rough after all.

03:42.304 --> 03:45.105
all: Aloha, Lincoln.

03:45.107 --> 03:48.242
[light Hawaiian music]

03:48.244 --> 03:51.178
- What's that?
- It's your homework.

03:51.180 --> 03:52.179
All done.

03:52.181 --> 03:54.081
- Uh, you did it?

03:54.083 --> 03:55.849
- I did.
- Phew!

03:55.851 --> 03:58.051
I mean, not that it matters.

03:58.053 --> 03:59.686
[clown horn honks]
[gasps]

03:59.688 --> 04:02.055
- Hiya, Lincoln!

04:02.057 --> 04:03.657
- Tippy the cow!

04:03.659 --> 04:04.758
- Well, that's right!

04:04.760 --> 04:09.163
And guess what I have
for my favorite fan!

04:09.165 --> 04:11.698
- You did my laundry?
Wow.

04:11.700 --> 04:12.633
Thanks, Tippy.

04:12.635 --> 04:13.400
- You're welcome.

04:13.402 --> 04:15.002
[clown horn honks]
I'll see you soon

04:15.004 --> 04:21.875
at America's favorite
dairy-themed a-moo-sement park!

04:21.877 --> 04:23.844
- Bye, Tippy!

04:23.846 --> 04:25.913
I love that cow.

04:25.915 --> 04:28.782
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

04:28.784 --> 04:31.251
- Welcome to your own
private beach

04:31.253 --> 04:36.790
where we have sun, sand,
and surf.

04:37.826 --> 04:39.760
- Don't forget screams.

04:39.762 --> 04:41.328
[girls gasp]
- [roars]

04:41.330 --> 04:42.262
[girls scream]

04:42.264 --> 04:43.363
- And if you vote Team Beach,

04:43.365 --> 04:45.399
the fun
will literally never stop.

04:45.401 --> 04:49.303
- Yeah. If you need anything
else, just give us a toot.

04:49.305 --> 04:51.805
[blows note on conch shell]

04:51.807 --> 04:53.874
<i>♪</i>

04:56.211 --> 04:57.377
- What's happening?

04:57.379 --> 04:58.812
- All aboard the I-Screamer!

04:58.814 --> 05:04.251
- Please keep your arms and legs
inside the ride at all times.

05:04.253 --> 05:05.385
- Woo-hoo!

05:05.387 --> 05:08.121
Faster, faster!

05:08.123 --> 05:08.989
[laughs]

05:08.991 --> 05:11.191
- Hope you enjoyed
the ride, bro.

05:11.193 --> 05:12.793
- If you vote for Dairyland,

05:12.795 --> 05:16.697
you'll have 2% more fun.
[laughs]

05:16.699 --> 05:19.399
- If you require our services...
[rings cowbell]

05:19.401 --> 05:21.401
Just call on Team Tippy.

05:21.403 --> 05:25.672
<i>[upbeat rock music]</i>

05:25.674 --> 05:26.773
[rings cowbell]

05:26.775 --> 05:30.444
<i>♪</i>

05:30.446 --> 05:32.446
[blows note on conch shell]

05:32.448 --> 05:35.148
<i>♪</i>

05:35.150 --> 05:36.216
[rings cowbell]

05:36.218 --> 05:37.885
<i>♪</i>

05:37.887 --> 05:39.253
[blows note on conch shell]

05:39.255 --> 05:41.922
<i>♪</i>

05:41.924 --> 05:42.990
[rings cowbell]

05:42.992 --> 05:46.059
<i>♪</i>

05:46.061 --> 05:47.427
[blows note on conch shell]

05:47.429 --> 05:48.795
<i>♪</i>

05:48.797 --> 05:49.863
[rings cowbell]

05:49.865 --> 05:51.932
<i>♪</i>

05:51.934 --> 05:53.267
- All right, Lincoln.

05:53.269 --> 05:54.401
Your time's up.

05:54.403 --> 05:55.402
What's it gonna be?

05:55.404 --> 05:58.805
- I know I said I'd decide
by the end of the day,

05:58.807 --> 06:00.874
but I'm still torn.

06:00.876 --> 06:03.410
Can I have just one more day?

06:03.412 --> 06:05.846
- Why, you lousy little--

06:05.848 --> 06:09.283
- Uh, not a problem.
[chuckles]

06:09.285 --> 06:10.450
We understand.

06:10.452 --> 06:13.287
- All right.
- For sure, Lincoln.

06:13.289 --> 06:14.454
- Can you blame me?

06:14.456 --> 06:15.322
No matter what I decide,

06:15.324 --> 06:17.858
five of them are still gonna
be mad at me,

06:17.860 --> 06:20.260
but this day has been amazing.

06:20.262 --> 06:24.231
So I figure why not take
advantage of it a little longer?

06:24.233 --> 06:26.800
<i>- Ugh! What are we going to do,</i>
<i>you guys?</i>

06:26.802 --> 06:30.137
We need to try harder to show
him why the beach is better.

06:30.139 --> 06:36.977
- Or maybe we show him
why Dairyland is worse.

06:38.279 --> 06:40.747
- Got to pee, got to pee,
got to pee!

06:40.749 --> 06:42.983
Note to self.
No more cocoa before bed.

06:42.985 --> 06:43.850
What's going on?

06:43.852 --> 06:45.519
- Waiting in line
for the bathroom.

06:45.521 --> 06:46.853
Better get used
to standing in lines

06:46.855 --> 06:49.423
if you're gonna vote
for Dairyland.

06:49.425 --> 06:52.526
- [yelping]
- [yawns]

06:52.528 --> 06:54.027
[toilet flushes]

06:54.029 --> 06:56.430
Ah! Ooh! Ah!

06:56.432 --> 06:57.898
Aah!

06:57.900 --> 06:58.432
<i>What?</i>

06:58.434 --> 07:02.536
"Sorry! This ride
is temporarily closed"?

07:02.538 --> 07:04.137
<i>No!</i>

07:04.139 --> 07:08.542
- Oh, so that's
how they want to play?

07:08.544 --> 07:10.110
- [whimpers]

07:10.112 --> 07:14.281
[water running]
Ahh, sweet relief!

07:14.283 --> 07:16.316
Ah! Freezing!

07:16.318 --> 07:18.051
What happened
to all the hot water?

07:18.053 --> 07:20.821
- You better get used to it
if you vote for the beach.

07:20.823 --> 07:23.857
- Because the average ocean
temperature

07:23.859 --> 07:27.160
is 16.6 degrees Celsius.

07:35.570 --> 07:36.503
- Uh, guys, FYI,

07:36.505 --> 07:41.441
sand in my crack does not make
me want to vote for the beach.

07:41.443 --> 07:43.310
[both laugh]

07:45.179 --> 07:46.980
<i>[rock music]</i>

07:46.982 --> 07:48.382
Guys! Guys, too fast!

07:48.384 --> 07:50.317
Too fast, guys!
Guys, too fast!

07:50.319 --> 07:53.954
I'm gonna hurl!
[vomits]

07:55.857 --> 07:56.523
Word of advice.

07:56.525 --> 08:01.194
Blowing chunks does not make me
want to vote for Dairyland.

08:02.497 --> 08:05.399
"Everything you'll need for fun
in the sun.

08:05.401 --> 08:09.102
Enjoy. Team Beach."

08:09.104 --> 08:11.038
SPF 800 sunscreen.

08:11.040 --> 08:14.908
Perfect for my fair skin.

08:14.910 --> 08:16.343
Hm, tingly.

08:16.345 --> 08:17.611
[skin sizzles]

08:17.613 --> 08:21.014
[bell rings]
Aah! News flash!

08:21.016 --> 08:24.051
Giving me a sunburn
is not the way to win my vote.

08:24.053 --> 08:27.854
- Huh?
Sodium hydrochlorite?

08:27.856 --> 08:29.289
"Avoid contact with skin"?

08:29.291 --> 08:32.125
This has Lisa written
all over it.

08:32.126 --> 08:36.063
- So that's how you spell Lisa?

08:36.065 --> 08:37.864
[clown horn honks]
- [gasps]

08:37.866 --> 08:39.933
Tippy!
Ah!

08:39.934 --> 08:41.368
Mad cow!
Mad cow!

08:41.370 --> 08:42.869
<i>[screaming]</i>

08:42.871 --> 08:44.971
<i>[grunting]</i>

08:46.207 --> 08:47.307
[sighs]

08:47.309 --> 08:48.275
- Well?

08:48.277 --> 08:49.543
- Worked like a charm.

08:49.545 --> 08:51.611
Aloha Beach is in our future.

08:51.613 --> 08:52.979
- We knew it!

08:52.981 --> 08:55.549
You've been sabotaging us.

08:55.551 --> 08:57.017
- We sabotaged you?

08:57.019 --> 08:59.052
You put sand
in Lincoln's underpants.

08:59.054 --> 09:02.322
- But you started it
with the line for the bathroom.

09:02.324 --> 09:05.392
[overlapping arguing]

09:05.394 --> 09:06.426
- [groans]

09:06.428 --> 09:09.162
[rings cowbell and blows conch]

09:09.164 --> 09:11.198
<i>Can I get an ice pack?</i>

09:11.200 --> 09:13.333
<i>Some bandages?</i>

09:13.335 --> 09:14.468
<i>A hug?</i>

09:14.470 --> 09:16.203
Where is everybody?

09:16.205 --> 09:17.504
[overlapping arguing]

09:17.506 --> 09:19.039
<i>[rings cowbell and blows conch]</i>

09:19.041 --> 09:20.040
I'm blowing the conch,

09:20.042 --> 09:23.143
I'm ringing the bell,
and yet, nothing.

09:23.145 --> 09:23.710
- You!

09:23.712 --> 09:26.279
This is all your fault.
- Yeah.

09:26.281 --> 09:28.181
If you had just made up
your mind,

09:28.183 --> 09:30.250
none of this
would have happened.

09:30.252 --> 09:32.285
[overlapping arguing]

09:32.287 --> 09:34.154
- Great.
I was afraid of making

09:34.156 --> 09:36.123
five of my sisters mad at me,

09:36.125 --> 09:37.424
but now all ten are.

09:37.426 --> 09:39.526
There's only one thing
left to do.

09:39.528 --> 09:41.928
- Fine with us, sweetie.
- Sure, son.

09:41.930 --> 09:43.396
I don't see why not.

09:43.398 --> 09:45.031
- Quiet down!

09:45.033 --> 09:46.166
I've made my decision.

09:46.168 --> 09:50.036
We're going
to Scratchy Bottom Campgrounds!

09:50.038 --> 09:52.472
all: What?
- But what about the bears?

09:52.474 --> 09:55.142
- And the Dipterum Culicidae
bites?

09:55.144 --> 09:56.243
- And the pooping
in the woods?

09:56.245 --> 09:58.445
- That's still the only reason
I'd go.

09:58.447 --> 10:03.150
- Ugh, this is literally going
to be the worst vacation ever.

10:03.152 --> 10:07.354
This is literally
the best vacation ever.

10:07.356 --> 10:08.688
[overlapping agreements]

10:08.690 --> 10:11.458
- Why were we
so against this place?

10:11.460 --> 10:12.526
[rings cowbell]

10:12.528 --> 10:16.530
<i>♪</i>

10:16.532 --> 10:19.566
<i>- [blows conch shell]</i>
<i>- [rings cowbell]</i>

10:19.568 --> 10:21.234
- Ah!

10:21.236 --> 10:22.969
Ooh!
[grunts]

10:22.971 --> 10:23.603
[screams]

10:23.605 --> 10:25.105
<i>- [blows conch shell]</i>

10:25.107 --> 10:26.106
- [screams]

10:26.108 --> 10:27.307
<i>- [rings cowbell]</i>

10:27.309 --> 10:31.444
<i>♪</i>

10:31.446 --> 10:33.513
- It may not be much
of a vacation for me,

10:33.515 --> 10:36.716
but it's worth it if all ten
of my sisters are happy.

10:36.718 --> 10:40.387
I'd say
everything turned out A-okay.

10:40.389 --> 10:42.255
[sinister laughter]

10:42.257 --> 10:42.889
[screams]

10:42.891 --> 10:46.059
The hill people
hiding in the trees!

10:48.196 --> 10:49.696
<i>- ♪ Cramped inside</i>
<i>this tiny space ♪</i>

10:49.698 --> 10:51.498
<i>♪ May sound bad</i>
<i>but ain't the case ♪</i>

10:51.500 --> 10:54.434
<i>♪ In the Loud house</i>
<i>- ♪ Loud house</i>

10:54.436 --> 10:56.603
<i>- ♪ Duck and dodge</i>
<i>and push and shove ♪</i>

10:56.605 --> 11:01.508
<i>♪ That's the way we show our</i>
<i>love in the Loud house ♪</i>

11:01.510 --> 11:02.542
<i>- ♪ Loud house</i>

11:02.544 --> 11:04.110
<i>♪ Laundry piles</i>
<i>stacked up high ♪</i>

11:04.112 --> 11:05.445
<i>♪ Hand-me-downs</i>
<i>that make me cry ♪</i>

11:05.447 --> 11:06.780
<i>♪ Stand in line to take a pee</i>

11:06.782 --> 11:08.281
<i>♪ Never any privacy</i>

11:08.283 --> 11:10.450
<i>♪ Chaos with 11 kids</i>

11:10.452 --> 11:13.353
<i>♪ That's the way</i>
<i>it always is ♪</i>

11:13.355 --> 11:15.288
<i>♪ In the Loud house</i>
